The paper deals with secure transmission in a massive MIMO system, which involves information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), control theory (cs.SY), multimedia (cs.MM), and cryptography and security (cs.CR). The focus on linear precoding and optimization techniques also suggests a strong connection to signal processing (cs.SP). However, since the paper primarily addresses the security aspects of the system, we consider cs.CR to be the least likely category.
